=== Myalgia (Muscle Pain)
<subsec:myalgia>

*Clinical Presentation.*

    - Widespread muscle aching and soreness
    - Deep muscle pain, often described as "flu-like"
    - Pain worsening with activity or pressure
    - Muscle tenderness to palpation
    - Delayed-onset muscle soreness after minimal exertion
    - Persistent muscle tension

*Mechanism.*
Myalgia reflects lactic acid accumulation from anaerobic metabolism, muscle hypoxia, central sensitization amplifying pain signals, and possible muscle microtrauma from energy-deficient muscle fibers.
